**kubernetes**


<< Nodes-- k8s nodes has -- 

pods run on nodes

Node has Rootns



           Pod
            |
           podns
            |
this is Linux Networking Stack
            |
Ethernet, routing, iptables, conntracking.


CNI - Computer Network Interface- cni plugin is required to implement the kubernetes network model.







In Kubernetes, there are Two types of Nodes.
One is Master-node(Control-Plane). Second is WorkeR-node.

Master-node Consist of an Architecture which is.
1. Kube-apiserver= the Entry-point -of all Commands
2. ETCD - use for data Storage.
3. Scheduler - they Decide which pod will Be in which Node.
4. Controll Manager - use to maintain the actual stage from the desired stage which is described in YAML file .

Worker-Node Consist of an Architecture which is.
1. Kubelet -
2. Kube-proxy - use to manage Network of pod , to available for outer world.

**Deploymentset**
basically used for apps, and to make the replicas of pod as a backup,if any case a pod is delete then there is a another pod also.
which will be created automatically without resistance.

**Statefulset**
used for basically database, and it makes a pod in a sequence-- like 1,2,3,4-and all, in the last of the pod
if a pod-1 is delete then it will exactly make a pod of (1) only, unlike deploymentset

**DaemonSet**
it basically used to make one pod on each node & used to store log. 


